title.narrative: Danish support to Kosovo's Agriculture Sector Strategy , engagement

description.narrative: Approximately 60% of the population of Kosovo lives in rural areas, which is also where unemployment and poverty are most prevalent. The overarching aim of the support is to raise the living standards and employment in the agricultural sector as well as supporting Kosovo's EU-integration, by supporting the implementation of the national strategy for agriculture and rural development. The implementation of the national strategy is supported through two components: (A) Investment capital for the national agricultural matching grant scheme as well as technical support for capacity building in the Ministry of Agriculture (through a delegated partnership with the World Bank as well as an international long-term Danida adviser) and (B) support for female entrepreneurs in the agricultural sector through Kosovo's Women's Business Association.
